====張成澤“被犬決”====
<!-- 注释出：[[File:張成澤.jpg|thumb]]委員和朝鮮勞動黨中央行政部部長[[張成澤|張成澤]]被香港《文匯報》誤指為被狗活活咬死。]] -->

曾擔任[[朝鮮勞動黨中央政治局|朝鮮勞動黨中央政治局]]委員和朝鮮勞動黨中央行政部部長等要職的[[張成澤|張成澤]]在2013年12月12日因叛國等罪名被判死刑。香港《[[文匯報_(香港)|文匯報]]》稱張成澤並非被槍斃，而是在金正恩和300名官員的目睹下被120頭狗活活咬死<ref>{{cite news|title=Kim Jong-Un's uncle stripped naked and fed to 120 starving dogs as tyrant watched|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/north-korea-kim-jong-uns-uncle-2983138|first1=Chris|last1=Hughes|first2=Paul|last2=Cockerton|newspaper=Mirror|date=2014-01-03|access-date=2017-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919105734/http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/north-korea-kim-jong-uns-uncle-2983138|archive-date=2016-09-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。之後，《[[NBC新聞|NBC新聞]]》、《[[泰晤士報|泰晤士報]]》及《[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]》等均引述此報導。不過，《[[BBC|BBC]]》和《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》等都懷疑這事的真實性<ref>{{cite news|title=金正恩「犬決」張成澤真有其事？|url=http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/world/2014/01/140104_blog_north_korea_chang|author=安東尼·澤克|newspaper=BBC|date=2014-01-04|access-date=2017-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007124836/http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/world/2014/01/140104_blog_north_korea_chang|archive-date=2017-10-07|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=金正恩放狗咬死姑父的傳聞引發猜測|url=https://cn.nytimes.com/asia-pacific/20140106/c06execution/zh-hant/|author=黃安偉|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2014-01-06|access-date=2017-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007121645/https://cn.nytimes.com/asia-pacific/20140106/c06execution/zh-hant/|archive-date=2017-10-07|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在韩国，亦鮮有傳媒引用《文匯報》的報導。在一個月後，芝加哥一名軟件工程師發現張成澤遭到犬決是出自於一個惡搞朝鲜的中國博客<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/01/06/jang-song-thaek-eaten-by-dog_n_4547814.html |title=Jang Song Thaek Eaten By Dog Story Likely Came From Satire |date=2014-01-06 |agency=Reuters |publisher=Huffington Post |accessdate=2014-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109163427/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/01/06/jang-song-thaek-eaten-by-dog_n_4547814.html |archive-date=2014-01-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此消息傳出後，部份傳媒決定收回之前關於犬決的報導。

====玄松月“被處決”====
2013年8月29日，《[[朝鮮日報|朝鮮日報]]》聲稱金正恩的前女友、[[牡丹峰樂團|牡丹峰樂團]]團長[[玄松月|玄松月]]因製作和銷售淫穢物品而被公開槍決<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/hyon-song-wol-pornographic-video-kim-jong-un-ex-girlfriend-2013-9 |title=Hyon Song-Wol 'Pornographic' Video - Kim Jong-Un Ex-Girlfriend |publisher=Business Insider |date=2013-09-05 |accessdate=2014-05-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607060250/http://www.businessinsider.com/hyon-song-wol-pornographic-video-kim-jong-un-ex-girlfriend-2013-9 |archive-date=2014-06-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。美國[[自由亞洲電台|自由亞洲電台]]更指玄氏是因向身邊人透露與金正恩的關係才遭到殺身之禍<ref name="joins">{{cite web |url=http://chinese.joins.com/gb/article.do?method=detail&art_id=119701 |title=被传“遭到枪决”的朝鲜牡丹峰乐团团长玄松月仍在进行活动 |publisher=[[中央日報_(韓國)|韓國中央日报]] |date=2014-05-17 |accessdate=2014-05-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304081610/http://chinese.joins.com/gb/article.do?method=detail&art_id=119701 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[Daily_NK|Daily NK]]》認為金正恩是在「非常憤怒」下才將玄氏公開處決<ref name="joins"/>。朝鮮中央通訊社率先否認傳聞，一部日本政治雜誌隨後亦報稱玄氏未死。2014年5月16日， 玄氏出席朝鲜第9屆全國藝術家大會，粉碎了傳言<ref name="joins"/>。

====李永吉“被處決”====
[[韓聯社|韓聯社]]在2016年2月10日宣稱朝鮮人民軍總參謀長[[李永吉|李永吉]]被處死，罪名是「宗派分子和專權腐敗」，理據是他缺席早前舉行的朝鮮勞動黨中央委員會與朝鮮勞動黨朝鮮人民軍委員會聯合會議擴大會議<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kim Jong-un has reportedly just executed the chief of his own military|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/north-korea-kim-jong-un-executes-chief-of-military-on-corruption-charges-a6864571.html|website=The Independent|accessdate=2016-07-01|last=Withnall|first=Adam|date=2016-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623133356/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/north-korea-kim-jong-un-executes-chief-of-military-on-corruption-charges-a6864571.html|archive-date=2016-06-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同年5月，「被處決」的李永吉在[[朝鮮勞動黨第七次代表大會|朝鮮勞動黨第七次代表大會]]上被委任為中央委員會委員、政治局候補委員及中央軍事委員會委員<ref>{{cite news|title=前朝鮮軍方三號人物李永吉「死而復生」|url=https://cn.nytimes.com/asia-pacific/20160511/c11northkorea/zh-hant/|author=CHOE SANG-HUN|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2016-05-11|accessdate=2021-02-05|archive-date=2019-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816030635/https://cn.nytimes.com/asia-pacific/20160511/c11northkorea/zh-hant/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

